Turner, Young and Hawes gave no indication that they give any less than what is expected of them, and Anderson is showing a real knack for getting the ball to the rim. As fast as the pace was, Tony Wroten was still a step ahead of it off the bench, and Lavoy Allen did a good job of rebounding (nine in 16 minutes), though his conditioning still appears to be nowhere close to prime.
